      "date": "2013-01-07 19:33:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nTesting this in a local VM setup, I'm hitting this assertion:\n\n    LustreError: 32373:0:(osd_handler.c:1609:osd_attr_set()) ASSERTION( (oh)->ot_declare_attr_set > 0 ) failed:!\n    LustreError: 32373:0:(osd_handler.c:1609:osd_attr_set()) LBUG                  \n    Kernel panic - not syncing: LBUG                                               \n    Pid: 32373, comm: mdt00_001 Tainted: P           ---------------    2.6.32-279.9.1.1chaos.ch5.1.x86_64 #1\n    Call Trace:                                                                    \n     [<ffffffff814fdceb>] ? panic+0xa0/0x168                                       \n     [<ffffffffa06fff6b>] ? lbug_with_loc+0x9b/0xb0 [libcfs]                       \n     [<ffffffffa0e28f9b>] ? osd_attr_set+0x23b/0x240 [osd_ldiskfs]                 \n     [<ffffffffa0f615d3>] ? lod_attr_set+0x133/0x470 [lod]                         \n     [<ffffffffa0d3d79b>] ? mdd_attr_set_internal+0x8b/0x340 [mdd]                 \n     [<ffffffffa0d3dcc5>] ? mdd_attr_check_set_internal+0x275/0x2c0 [mdd]          \n     [<ffffffffa0d50105>] ? mdd_create+0x1025/0x14e0 [mdd]                         \n     [<ffffffffa0ed7007>] ? mdt_reint_open+0x1077/0x1850 [mdt]                     \n     [<ffffffffa0840ce0>] ? lu_ucred+0x20/0x30 [obdclass]                          \n     [<ffffffffa0ea1765>] ? mdt_ucred+0x15/0x20 [mdt]                              \n     [<ffffffffa0ec1e11>] ? mdt_reint_rec+0x41/0xe0 [mdt]                          \n     [<ffffffffa0ebb2d3>] ? mdt_reint_internal+0x4f3/0x7f0 [mdt]                   \n     [<ffffffffa0ebb89d>] ? mdt_intent_reint+0x1ed/0x500 [mdt]                     \n     [<ffffffffa0eb7215>] ? mdt_intent_policy+0x3c5/0x800 [mdt]                    \n     [<ffffffffa09949d1>] ? ldlm_lock_enqueue+0x361/0x8f0 [ptlrpc]                 \n     [<ffffffffa09bd987>] ? ldlm_handle_enqueue0+0x4f7/0x1090 [ptlrpc]             \n     [<ffffffffa0eb77a6>] ? mdt_enqueue+0x46/0x130 [mdt]                           \n     [<ffffffffa0eaa952>] ? mdt_handle_common+0x932/0x1750 [mdt]                   \n     [<ffffffffa0eab845>] ? mdt_regular_handle+0x15/0x20 [mdt]                     \n     [<ffffffffa09eda0c>] ? ptlrpc_server_handle_request+0x41c/0xe00 [ptlrpc]   \n     [<ffffffffa070065e>] ? cfs_timer_arm+0xe/0x10 [libcfs]                        \n     [<ffffffffa09e4df9>] ? ptlrpc_wait_event+0xa9/0x290 [ptlrpc]                  \n     [<ffffffff81053443>] ? __wake_up+0x53/0x70                                    \n     [<ffffffffa09eefa5>] ? ptlrpc_main+0xbb5/0x1970 [ptlrpc]                      \n     [<ffffffffa09ee3f0>] ? ptlrpc_main+0x0/0x1970 [ptlrpc]                        \n     [<ffffffff8100c14a>] ? child_rip+0xa/0x20                                     \n     [<ffffffffa09ee3f0>] ? ptlrpc_main+0x0/0x1970 [ptlrpc]                        \n     [<ffffffffa09ee3f0>] ? ptlrpc_main+0x0/0x1970 [ptlrpc]                        \n     [<ffffffff8100c140>] ? child_rip+0x0/0x20\n\nAlso, since we have a simple reproducer listed in the bug, we should also add a test case with the fix.\n\n    $ mkdir $tdir\n    $ cd $tdir\n    $ getfacl --access . | setfacl -d -M - .\n    $ touch $tfile\n    $ <insert check for file size of 0> && return 0 || return 1\n\nOr something along those lines.",
